      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A healthy sourdough starter is thriving when it's bubbly, frothy, and has a slightly puffed or rounded appearance. A well-balanced community typically presents a uniform texture, with bubbles of varying sizes, distributing relatively evenly throughout the starter. On the other hand, an imbalanced or unhealthy starter may exhibit unusual textures, such as an overly dense or separated mass. Signs of an unhealthy community could also include excessive mold growth, unusual odors, or a sudden decrease in activity. A starter that becomes too actively soupy or too separated is likely a sign of an overgrowth of lactobacilli, while a starter that seems too dense or thick may indicate an overgrowth of yeast.",
